{
 "base_path": "/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim43100",
 "body": "<h2>Intangible Assets</h2>\n<p>In relation to expenditure by companies in respect of intangible fixed assets see <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/corporate-intangibles-research-and-development-manual/cird12610\" rel=\"nofollow\">CIRD12610</a>.</p>\n<h2>Contact with Business Profits</h2>\n<p>Because of the nature of the legislation and the complexity of law relating to such criminal offences you should contact&nbsp;<span>Business Profits</span>&nbsp;at an early stage if you discover payments subject to the legislation.</p>\n<p>A deduction is not allowable for certain crime-related payments in calculating the profits of a trade. This chapter describes the legislation and how it works. It is arranged as follows:</p>\n",
